==English==
===Etymology===
from Spanish ''embargar'' 'to arrest'
===Pronunciation===
IPA (''US''):  /əmˈbɑrgoʊ/
===Noun===
'''embargo''' (plural: [[embargoes]])

#an [[order]] by the government [[prohibit]]ing [[ship]]s from leaving [[port]]
#a [[ban]] on [[trade]] with another country
#*Several countries have imposed an '''embargo''' on Burma.
#a temporary [[ban]] on making certain [[information]] public
#*This copy of the federal budget is under '''embargo''' until 2 p.m.

===Transitive verb===
'''embargo'''
# to impose an embargo on trading certain goods with another country
# to impose an embargo on a document

